<Window x:Class="HangManV01.Views.Rules"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:HangManV01"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Title="Rules" Height="550" Width="830" Icon="/Assets/Images/icon.ico">
    <Grid Background="#333333">
        <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
            <TextBlock HorizontalAlignment="Center" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" Margin="30" Foreground="White" Background="#333333" FontSize="16">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="18" Text="Objective:"/><LineBreak/>
                The player aims to guess a word or phrase before the hangman figure is fully drawn.

                <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
                <Run FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="18" Text="Setup:"/><LineBreak/>
                A computer program randomly selects a word or phrase or gets one from another player, and displays blanks for each letter. For example, for the word "COMPUTER", it would display: _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _.

                <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
                <Run FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="18" Text="How to Play:"/><LineBreak/>
                <Run Text="1. Guessing Letters: "/> The player guesses a letter of the word. If the letter is in the word, the program fills it in the appropriate blank(s).<LineBreak/>
                <Run Text="2. Incorrect Guesses: "/> For every incorrect letter guessed, a part of the hangman figure is drawn.<LineBreak/>
                <Run FontWeight="Bold" Text="3. Winning or Losing:"/><LineBreak/>
                - Winning: The player wins by guessing all the letters in the word before the hangman is fully drawn.<LineBreak/>
                - Losing: The player loses if the hangman is fully drawn before all the letters in the word are guessed.

                <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
                <Run FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="18" Text="Computer Features:"/><LineBreak/>
                
                
                - A visual representation of the hangman structure gets updated with every wrong guess.

                <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
                <Run FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="18" Text="Tips:"/><LineBreak/>
                - Use hint to make the game more easy.<LineBreak/>
                - The difficulty level can be adjusted by the length of the word.
            </TextBlock>
        </ScrollViewer>
        <Button  Content="Back" HorizontalAlignment="Right" VerticalAlignment="Top" Margin="0,469,60,0" Width="100" Height="30" Background="#FF0000" Foreground="#FFFFFF" FontSize="16" Click="BackButton_Click"/>
    </Grid>
</Window>